---
// Breast Surgery Houston, TX
// Ported from: breast-surgery-houston.php
export const prerender = true;

import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import CategoryGrid from "../components/CategoryGrid.astro";
import { CATEGORIES_TOP } from "../lib/categories";
---

<Base
  title="Breast Surgery Houston, TX | The Oaks Plastic Surgery"
  description="Breast Surgery Houston, TX at The Oaks Plastic Surgery. Board-certified plastic surgeons offering personalized care."
  headerTitle="Breast Surgery Houston, TX"
  headerImage="/img/mom-hero.jpg"
  headerMarginBottom={60}
  canonical="https://theoaksplasticsurgery.com/breast-surgery-houston"
>
<section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
                            <p class="wow fadeInUp lead text-center">
                               
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-0 pb-240">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>  
            
            <section class="text-section pb-240">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <h2 class="wow fadeInUp center text-center">What breast surgeries are offered at TOPS Houston?</h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3><a href="/breast-augmentation-houston">Breast Augmentation</a></h3>
                                <p>
                                    TOPS Houston offers a variety of breast augmentation options. After speaking extensively with Dr. Andry or Dr. Wijay, patients can determine details like the site of their incisions, the placement of their implants in relation to the muscle, the size and fill of their implants, and the type (saline or silicone) of their implants. This doctor-patient collaboration ensures that your cosmetic surgeon fully understands your goals and you fully understand your procedure.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3><a href="/breast-lift-surgery-houston">Breast Lift</a></h3>
                                <p>
                                    After pregnancy, nursing, and weight loss, many women experience significant sagging and deflation of the breasts. When you’re seeking to restore breasts’ former perkiness, your plastic surgeon may recommend breast lift surgery or mastopexy. This breast surgery results in higher, more youthful looking breasts and can be performed with or without augmentation.
                                </p>
                            </div>                            
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3><a href="/breast-reduction-houston">Breast Reduction</a></h3>
                                <p>
                                   Our breast reduction patients often experience back, neck, and shoulder pain as well as frustration finding and fitting into bras and clothing. Breast reduction surgery can offer relief from sore back and shoulders and is frequently performed along with breast lift surgery. 
                                </p>
                            </div>                            
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3><a href="/gynecomastia-houston">Male Breast Reduction</a></h3>
                                <p>
                                    Gynecomastia is a common but embarrassing and frustrating condition for many men. In the normal population greater than 50% of men are affected by gynecomastia. Usually weight loss and exercise are not enough to completely correct it. Male breast reduction surgery at TOPS Houston can help.
                                </p>
                            </div>                            
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3><a href="/breast-reconstruction-houston">Breast Reconstruction</a></h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Breast reconstruction is most commonly performed after mastectomies and lumpectomies for cancer but is also commonly performed for congenital abnormalities and disfiguring accidents. Breast reconstruction surgery utilizes implants or the patient’s own tissue to restore a natural shape and fullness to the breasts.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    For many patients, the loss of their breasts was an emotionally taxing or even traumatic experience. At TOPS Houston, your breast reconstruction will be handled with compassion and sensitivity, making it an emotionally healing experience as well as a physical one.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3><a href="/breast-implant-removal">Breast Implant Removal</a></h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Some women with breast implants eventually want to have them removed or replaced due to complications or a desire to return to smaller breasts. Sometimes called “explant” surgery, breast implant removal involves removing the implant and occasionally the surrounding scar tissue or “capsule”. Because implants can eventually cause deflation or stretching of the surrounding breast tissue, many women also choose to have a breast lift at the time of their implant removal.
                                </p>
                            </div>                            
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3><a href="/inverted-nipple-houston">Inverted Nipple</a></h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Though inverted nipples are common, many men and women who have them want them corrected to improve the aesthetic appearance of their breast or chest. Though inverted nipple correction is a relatively simple cosmetic procedure, it does make breastfeeding impossible and should be delayed for any woman who plans to nurse future children. 
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3><a href="/nipple-reduction-houston">Nipple Reduction</a></h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                   Nipple reductions can improve the appearance of overly enlarged nipples and make clothing more comfortable. Nipple reductions are often performed along with other cosmetic surgeries like breast augmentation or male breast reduction surgery for gynecomastia. 
                                </p>
                            </div>                            
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="text-section pb-240">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <h2 class="wow fadeInUp center text-center"><a href="/contact-us">Schedule your initial consultation</a> or reach out to the staff at The Oak Plastic Surgery Houston to learn how we can meet your breast surgery needs.</h2>
                    </div>
                </div>                               
            </section>                       
            <section>
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    <div class="row">
                        
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
  <section>
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <div class="row">
        <CategoryGrid categories={CATEGORIES_TOP} />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
